Description: At our core, Pariveda wants to gain the trust of clients in managing their financial assets.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: At our core, Pariveda wants to gain the trust of clients in managing their financial assets. The trust relationship begins when potential investors can see — for free — how well our performance has been on a quarter by quarter basis.  Unlike many other investment advisors, Pariveda has nothing to hide with regards to our performance.  Other financial advisors might say “just trust us, we know what we’re doing,” but will they open up their financial performance data? Knowledge, honesty, and “openness” are the important factors in developing a trusting environment between a client and Pariveda. Pariveda, Inc. is a privately held, fee-only Registered Investment Advisor serving the wealth management needs of individual and corporate clients across the United States. We currently manage client assets from our office located inMenlo Park, California. Simply stated, Pariveda’s goal is to outperform the market by 3-5% over a complete cycle (and on an after-fee basis). Most academic research reports that an investor cannot beat the market rate of return.  Perhaps the financial services firms have realized this because they offer index or life cycle mutual funds which basically follow the market indexes like the Standard & Poors. But at Pariveda, if we cannot outperform the market by 3-5%, then you should take your money and invest in one of these index-like funds. Pariveda has no potential conflicts of interest that could adversely affect our performance and we receive no commissions or incentives to cloud our investment judgment. We simply evaluate the investment landscape for the most attractive offerings in each market sector and allocate client assets appropriately.

Full Description: Value Plus Ventures is founded on the premise that successful companies share, at a minimum, four common traits. The Venture Capital community has transitioned throughout the past decade from start up funding to Growth Equity investment.  Capital is readily available today for companies with a proven business model and a management team, which can execute against that model. However, the challenge today for early stage companies is that without capital, it is difficult to develop a proven business model and to attract a "fundable" management team.   Value Plus Ventures addresses this challenge by providing both management and capital to emerging companies. Management expertise is provided through an array of sources in a cash friendly structure. The management sources range from partner involvement to Value Plus’ advisor's network. This expertise is designed to mentor, not replace, the existing team although in some cases there may be the need for a more long term senior management solution.

Full Description: In 2004, Steven Laken, Ph.D. founded Cephos on the basic principle of getting to the truth. Dr. Laken is a pioneer in the biotechnology field and a qualified DNA expert, with a rich history of forging breakthroughs in molecular testing and product development, clinical studies, and brain-based lie detection. He holds four patents in detecting and testing a familial genetic mutation that causes colorectal cancer, and two in measuring and testing brain activity for lie detection. The American Cancer Society and the American Society of Clinical Oncologists now recommend genetic testing based on his work in the latter patents.  In 2008, Cephos expanded its commercial offerings to include DNA evidence work to aid lawyers in the growing demand for investigation of civil and criminal investigations. More recently, Cephos has teamed up with leading biotech firms on the strategy and development of innovative products and commercial diagnostic tests based on genetic markers. Cephos is a CPCS-approved vendor, proud provider to the Public Defender's Office in Massachusetts, and has worked with numerous clients who have been wrongfully convicted of crimes they did not commit.
